summary.intent: Merge the latest changes from origin/main into the current branch to stay up-to-date with upstream developments.
summary.outcome: Successfully resolved merge conflict in manual_commit_hooks.go by combining the branch's improved isSpecificAgentType check with main's new LastInteractionAt timestamp tracking. All tests passed and changes were pushed.

repo: The codebase recently added LastInteractionAt timestamp tracking, FirstPrompt field, and truncatePromptForStorage function to the strategy package
Build failures after merges can sometimes be stale LSP diagnostics rather than actual compilation errors

code.finding: Merge conflict pattern: branch had improved isSpecificAgentType logic while main added LastInteractionAt timestamp - both changes were compatible and needed

workflow: After resolving merge conflicts, verify compilation of specific packages before running full test suite to catch issues early
Standard merge workflow: resolve conflicts, format/lint, run tests, then commit and push

friction: Initial build failure after conflict resolution was misleading (stale LSP diagnostics vs actual compilation errors)
